Subject: Re: [T2] Stuck Spark Plugs

No, you should use a penetrating oil, not a water displacer.  I use  
AeroKroil. Yon might try Liquid Wrench. WD40 is NOT penetrating oil.  
It's deodorized kerosene used for driving the water away (or as  
starting fluid for reluctant diesels.)

Jim

